  "title": "Youth Worker |School",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Services required are set out as follows:</strong></p><p>1. Outreach and engagement - engage and build positive</p><p>relationships with identified students during and/or outside</p><p>of curriculum hours (e.g. night, school holidays,</p><p>weekends), engage and connect with identified students</p><p>in school and/or community settings outside of school</p><p>compound, strongly encourage identified students to</p><p>attend school or after-school/community programmes,</p><p>and equip students with essential socio-emotional</p><p>knowledge and skills;</p><p>2.School collaboration – provide proper documentation,</p><p>relevant feedback and progress of students to school</p><p>personnel, and provide support and consultation to school</p><p>teachers on students’ needs and challenges;</p><p>3.Case management and Family Engagement – provide</p><p>case planning, management and counselling support to</p><p>the family, and conduct family engagement and</p><p>interventions;</p><p>4.Youth Worker for each school to be deployed only to the</p><p>school;</p><p>5.Assignment of Youth Worker should ensure continuity and</p><p>sustainability in the engagement of the identified students</p>",
